Garcinia multiflora

    Authority   Champ. ex Benth.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Guttiferales:Guttiferae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 6353

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A small evergreen tree reaching 10-15 m in height.
   Leaves oblong, 10 cm long, Fruit a fleshy berry, reddish. USES The
   fruit is used as a lemon substitute, an oil expressed from the seeds is
   used for lighting and the tree is used for shade in tea plantations.
   GROWING PERIOD Perennial. COMMON NAMES Bira tai, Cay gioc. FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: G. tonkinensis. Bira tai occurs in Southern China,
   northern Laos, Vietnam and Taiwan. The tree is well adapted to shade
   and humid conditions. Flowering usually occur after pronounced dry
   weather and often twice a year.

   Sources
   Verheij E 1991 pp 338 [USE, LIG]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 200 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 17 [PH, TEMP, RAIN]

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
